---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Sugar Trading | Buyer Access — ALFArhan General Trading Co."
  description="Structured buyer access for bulk sugar trade engagement across supported origins and destination routes."
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  locale="en"
  currentPath="commodities/sugar"
>
  <!-- [1] HERO -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Bulk Sugar Trading & Buyer Access</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Structured buyer access to Brazilian sugar trading markets through clear trade engagement and controlled execution.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a href="/en/contact" class="rounded bg-slate-900 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-slate-800">Request Buyer Access</a>
      <a href="#trade-routes" class="rounded border border-slate-300 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-50">View Trade Routes</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- [2] INTRO — COMMODITY POSITIONING -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Buyer-Focused Sugar Trading</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      AL Farhan General Trading Co. operates as a buyer-first trading intermediary, supporting international buyers engaged in bulk sugar trade within the Brazilian market.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Our role centers on facilitating market access, structuring engagement, and maintaining clarity throughout the trade process—without manufacturing, inventory, or ownership claims.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- [3] SUGAR TYPES — PRODUCT CLARITY -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Sugar Categories Covered</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Buyer engagement within the Brazilian sugar market commonly involves the following categories:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-3 pl-6 text-slate-600">
      <li>
        <strong class="text-slate-900">White Sugar — ICUMSA 45</strong><br />
        Refined white sugar widely used in food and beverage manufacturing and suitable for institutional and wholesale procurement.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-slate-900">Raw Sugar — Brown Sugar</strong><br />
        Unrefined or semi-refined sugar commonly utilized for further processing, refining, and industrial trade applications.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500">
      Product categories are listed for market orientation only and do not imply ownership.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- [4] MARKET ACCESS — BRAZIL ONLY -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Active Sugar Trading Market</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Sugar trade engagement under this category is oriented exclusively toward the Brazilian market, subject to specification alignment, destination requirements, and trade structure.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Market references are provided for orientation purposes only and do not imply ownership, exclusivity, or direct production.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- [5] TRADE ROUTES — CONTEXTUAL -->
  <section id="trade-routes" class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Indicative Trade Routes for Brazilian Sugar</h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 text-slate-600">
      <li>Brazil → Middle East</li>
      <li>Brazil → Africa</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500">
      Trade routes are indicative and aligned per buyer destination, specifications, and logistical considerations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- [6] HOW BUYER ENGAGEMENT WORKS -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">How Buyer Engagement Works</h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 text-slate-600">
      <li>Buyer inquiry and sugar category alignment</li>
      <li>Market orientation and trade framework discussion</li>
      <li>Structured communication and documentation</li>
      <li>Controlled facilitation through defined trade logic</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500">
      No pricing, guarantees, or inventory representations are displayed.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- [7] COMPLIANCE & CLARITY -->
  <section id="compliance" class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Clear, Buyer-Oriented Trade Framework</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      All sugar-related engagements are positioned within a clarity-first framework suitable for institutional review, procurement processes, and compliance consideration.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4">
      <a href="/en/contact" class="text-slate-600 underline hover:text-slate-900">View Compliance & KYC →</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- [8] FINAL CTA -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Proceed with Structured Brazilian Sugar Trade Engagement</h2>
    <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a href="/en/contact" class="rounded bg-slate-900 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-slate-800">Request Buyer Access</a>
      <a href="/en/contact" class="rounded border border-slate-300 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-50">Contact Our Team</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
